name: Ranggon Kedu
address: R472+4RC, Panji, Sukasada, Buleleng Regency, Bali 81161, Indonesia
review 1: The drive through the mountain incline was the perfect way to end up on a secluded rice field with a breath taking view. The rain season made this even better. Bring yourself a coffee and some cake, relax the afternoon and soak it in.
review 2: Great view and atmosphere. The shop dont have much in the menu.
review 3: Good vibes, but need efford to this place, they have standard foods like fried rice, etc.
review 4: One of the best rice field views of Bali nord. If you want to sit in one of the gazebo's, have to pay 5000 rp.
review 5: Visit this place if you ever going to panji village in Singaraja. Very beautiful view and a good place to enjoy a cup of Balinese coffee
